              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>3</fr:month>
              <fr:day>10</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000E/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>gtop-000E</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/gtop-000E/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Inner Regularity">Inner Regularity</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
A <fr:link href="/gtop-000C/" title="Borel Measure" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000C/" display-uri="gtop-000C" type="local">Borel measure</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu ]]></fr:tex> on a <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topological space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is <html:strong>inner regular</html:strong> on a <fr:link href="/gtop-000L/" title="Borel Set" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000L/" display-uri="gtop-000L" type="local">Borel set</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> if
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
\mu (E) = \sup  \left \{  \mu (M) : M \subseteq  E, \; M \text { is compact}  \right \}
]]></fr:tex>
where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/gtop-0008/" title="Compactness" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0008/" display-uri="gtop-0008" type="local">compact</fr:link> subset.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
That is, the measure of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> can be approximated from below by the measures of <fr:link href="/gtop-0008/" title="Compactness" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0008/" display-uri="gtop-0008" type="local">compact</fr:link> subsets of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>3</fr:month>
              <fr:day>10</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000O/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>gtop-000O</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/gtop-000O/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Locally Compact Space">Locally Compact Space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
A <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topological space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is <html:strong>locally compact</html:strong> if every point <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  X]]></fr:tex> has a <fr:link href="/gtop-000F/" title="Neighborhood" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000F/" display-uri="gtop-000F" type="local">neighbourhood</fr:link> contained in a <fr:link href="/gtop-0008/" title="Compactness" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0008/" display-uri="gtop-0008" type="local">compact</fr:link> subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>3</fr:month>
              <fr:day>10</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000D/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>gtop-000D</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/gtop-000D/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Outer Regularity">Outer Regularity</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
A <fr:link href="/gtop-000C/" title="Borel Measure" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000C/" display-uri="gtop-000C" type="local">Borel measure</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu ]]></fr:tex> on a <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topological space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is <html:strong>outer regular</html:strong> on a Borel set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> if
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
\mu (E) = \inf  \left \{  \mu (W) : E \subseteq  W, \; W \text { is open}  \right \}
]]></fr:tex>
where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link href="/gtop-0005/" title="Open Set" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0005/" display-uri="gtop-0005" type="local">open set</fr:link>.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
That is, the measure of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> can be approximated from above by the measures of <fr:link href="/gtop-0005/" title="Open Set" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0005/" display-uri="gtop-0005" type="local">open sets</fr:link> containing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>3</fr:month>
              <fr:day>7</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0008/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>gtop-0008</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/gtop-0008/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Compactness">Compactness</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
    A <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topological space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X, \tau )]]></fr:tex> is <html:strong>compact</html:strong> if every <fr:link href="/gtop-0007/" title="Open Cover" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0007/" display-uri="gtop-0007" type="local">open cover</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> has a <fr:link href="/gtop-0007/" title="Open Cover" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0007/" display-uri="gtop-0007" type="local">finite subcover</fr:link>.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
    A subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K \subseteq  X]]></fr:tex> is compact if it is compact as a topological space with the subspace topology, or equivalently, if every open cover of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> by open sets in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> has a finite subcover.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
    In <fr:link href="/gtop-0004/" title="Euclidean Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0004/" display-uri="gtop-0004" type="local">Euclidean space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex>, the Heine-Borel theorem gives a concrete characterization: a subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K \subseteq  \mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex> is compact if and only if it is <fr:link href="/gtop-0006/" title="Closed Set" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0006/" display-uri="gtop-0006" type="local">closed</fr:link> and bounded (i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K \subseteq  B(0, R)]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R > 0]]></fr:tex>).
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
              <fr:month>3</fr:month>
              <fr:day>7</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0005/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>gtop-0005</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/gtop-0005/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Open Set">Open Set</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
    Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X, \tau )]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topological space</fr:link>. A subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \subseteq  X]]></fr:tex> is called <html:strong>open</html:strong> if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \in  \tau ]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
    In a <fr:link href="/gtop-0004/" title="Euclidean Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0004/" display-uri="gtop-0004" type="local">Euclidean space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex>, a subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \subseteq  \mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex> is <html:strong>open</html:strong> if for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  U]]></fr:tex>, there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon  > 0]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B(x, \epsilon ) \subseteq  U]]></fr:tex>. More generally, in any <fr:link href="/gtop-0003/" title="Metric Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0003/" display-uri="gtop-0003" type="local">metric space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X, d)]]></fr:tex>, a set is open if it is a union of <fr:link href="/gtop-000S/" title="Open Ball" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000S/" display-uri="gtop-000S" type="local">open balls</fr:link>.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
    The <fr:link href="/gtop-0004/" title="Euclidean Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0004/" display-uri="gtop-0004" type="local">Euclidean</fr:link> definition is a special case where the topology is induced by the metric <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x, y) = \lVert  x - y \rVert ]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
